<subSubSection pageId="89" pageNumber="89" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="89.[128,654,1145,1759]" lastBlockId="89.[701,1228,213,264]" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">
<bibRefCitation author="Shelley, G. E." box="[157,390,1145,1168]" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" pagination="29 - 30" refId="ref128279" refString="Shelley, G. E. 1903. [Captain G. E. Shelley sent the following notes on the nomenclature of certain Fringillidae]. Bulletin of the British Ornithologists' Club 19: 29 - 30." type="journal article" year="1903">Shelley (1903: 30)</bibRefCitation>
proposed 
<taxonomicName class="Aves" family="Estrildidae" genus="Hypargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="harterti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">Hypargus harterti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a replacement name for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cabanis" authorityYear="1851" class="Aves" family="Estrildidae" genus="Lagonosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">Lagonosticta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(5 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shelley" authorityYear="1881" box="[235,347,1205,1226]" class="Aves" family="Estrildidae" genus="Hypargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[235,347,1205,1226]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">Hypargus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<taxonomicName authority="Hartlaub, 1886" authorityName="Hartlaub" authorityYear="1886" box="[368,650,1204,1227]" class="Aves" family="Estrildidae" genus="Lagonosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nitidula">
<emphasis box="[368,454,1204,1227]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">nitidula</emphasis>
Hartlaub, 1886
</taxonomicName>
, not 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swainson" authorityYear="1836" box="[175,270,1234,1257]" class="Aves" family="Estrildidae" genus="Estrelda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[175,270,1234,1257]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">Estrelda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(5 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shelley" authorityYear="1881" box="[317,429,1235,1256]" class="Aves" family="Estrildidae" genus="Hypargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[317,429,1235,1256]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">Hypargus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<taxonomicName authority="Hartlaub, 1885" authorityName="Hartlaub" authorityYear="1885" class="Aves" family="Estrildidae" genus="Lagonosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nitidula">
<emphasis box="[446,532,1234,1257]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">nitidula</emphasis>
Hartlaub, 1885
</taxonomicName>
, when the two nominal taxa are placed in the same genus. 
<taxonomicName box="[346,551,1293,1316]" class="Aves" family="Estrildidae" genus="Hypargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="harterti">
<emphasis box="[346,551,1293,1316]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">Hypargus harterti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
thus has the same 
<typeStatus box="[242,292,1323,1344]" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">type</typeStatus>
as 
<taxonomicName authority="Hartlaub, 1886" authorityName="Hartlaub" authorityYear="1886" class="Aves" family="Estrildidae" genus="Lagonosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nitidula">
<emphasis box="[336,579,1322,1345]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">Lagonosticta nitidula</emphasis>
Hartlaub, 1886
</taxonomicName>
, which is not in AMNH. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartert, E." pageId="89" pageNumber="89" pagination="123 - 178" refId="ref119004" refString="Hartert, E. 1919 a. Types of birds in the Tring Museum. B. Types in the general collection. Novitates Zoologicae 26: 123 - 178." type="journal article" year="1919">Hartert (1919a: 145–146)</bibRefCitation>
was in error when he attempted to typify Shelley’s name, 
<taxonomicName box="[561,646,1411,1434]" class="Aves" family="Estrildidae" genus="Hypargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="harterti">
<emphasis box="[561,646,1411,1434]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">harterti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with a specimen from Sagua, Quanza River, 
<collectingCountry box="[128,217,1471,1493]" name="Angola" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">Angola</collectingCountry>
, which 
<bibRefCitation author="Shelley, G. E." box="[318,536,1471,1493]" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" pagination="29 - 30" refId="ref128279" refString="Shelley, G. E. 1903. [Captain G. E. Shelley sent the following notes on the nomenclature of certain Fringillidae]. Bulletin of the British Ornithologists' Club 19: 29 - 30." type="journal article" year="1903">Shelley (1903: 30)</bibRefCitation>
said had convinced him that a new name was needed. That specimen is now AMNH 451305, male, collected at Sagua, Quanza River, on 
<date pageId="89" pageNumber="89" value="1901-05-21">21 May 1901</date>
, by C. Hubert Pemberton. For a discussion, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Chapin, J. P." box="[329,651,1618,1641]" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" pagination="1 - 846" refId="ref114020" refString="Chapin, J. P. 1954 b. The birds of the Belgian Congo, Part 4. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 75 B: i-ix, 1 - 846, 27 pls." type="book chapter" year="1954">Chapin (1954b: 531–533)</bibRefCitation>
. Because it bears a Rothschild 
<typeStatus box="[501,551,1649,1670]" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">type</typeStatus>
label, it remains in the AMNH 
<typeStatus box="[403,453,1678,1699]" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">type</typeStatus>
collection with a label added to explain its status. Because the two forms named 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hartlaub" authorityYear="1886" box="[337,423,1736,1759]" class="Aves" family="Estrildidae" genus="Lagonosticta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nitidula">
<emphasis box="[337,423,1736,1759]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">nitidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are no longer in the same genus, both of Hartlaub’s names may be used.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
